CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Prayer for Victory - On the V-E Day celebrated last Tuesday...Mrs. Ulysses Williams of Francis Street (center), mother of Pfc. Ulysses Williams Jr., who was killed in a vehicle accident while serving with a medical unit in Germany last February... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Gold Star mother Mrs. Ulysses Williams seated beside window in domestic interior
